  "title": "MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><strong>This is a Sichuan cuisine restaurant，we seek a talented and experienced restaurant manager to join our team</strong></p><h3><strong>Job Description</strong></h3><p>1. Responsible for the overall operation and management of the restaurant to ensure smooth daily operations;</p><p>2.Understand the unique flavors and cooking techniques of Sichuan cuisine, able to oversee the maintenance of dish quality and authenticity.</p><p>3.need to be familiar with Sichuan cuisine</p><p>4.Learn how to source Sichuan cuisine ingredients</p><p>5.Can manage Sichuan cuisine chefs</p><p>6. Develop and execute restaurant business plans to enhance performance;</p><p>7.ensure food safety and hygiene;</p><p>8. Be responsible for staff recruitment, training, performance evaluation, and team building;</p><p>9. Maintain good communication with customers to enhance customer satisfaction;</p><p>10.Preparing financial reports, including profit and loss statements, to assess the restaurant's financial performance.</p><p>11.Setting and monitoring budgets, including food and beverage costs, labor costs, and overhead expenses.</p><p>Tracking daily sales and expenses.</p><p>12. Complete other tasks assigned by superiors.</p><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><p>· Familiar with restaurant operation procedures and possess strong organizational, coordination, and communication skills;</p><p>· Passion for the catering industry and a keen interest in Sichuan cuisine ;</p><p>· Possess good team spirit and the ability to handle a certain level of work pressure.</p><p>· Proficient in Sichuan cuisine and have previous work experience in a Sichuan restaurant;</p><p><u><strong>· Able to work weekend and public holiday.</strong></u></p><p>We thank you for your interest and we regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. All resumes received will be used for recruitment purposes only.</p><p>EA License ID: 18C9520</p><p>EA Registration ID: R1765753</p>",
